{"data":{"wordpressPost":{"title":"Shopify Theme from Scratch Part 15: Theme Settings 2/2","content":"<html><head></head><body><p>\t\t\t\t<div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:23.25%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/0a29e347cf7b36c29637cdb3feebcdc2/19bd1/part15_banner.png 163w,\n/static/0a29e347cf7b36c29637cdb3feebcdc2/d3bcb/part15_banner.png 325w,\n/static/0a29e347cf7b36c29637cdb3feebcdc2/dbb61/part15_banner.png 650w,\n/static/0a29e347cf7b36c29637cdb3feebcdc2/8ff1e/part15_banner.png 800w\" src=\"/static/0a29e347cf7b36c29637cdb3feebcdc2/dbb61/part15_banner.png\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/0a29e347cf7b36c29637cdb3feebcdc2/19bd1/part15_banner.png 163w,\n/static/0a29e347cf7b36c29637cdb3feebcdc2/d3bcb/part15_banner.png 325w,\n/static/0a29e347cf7b36c29637cdb3feebcdc2/dbb61/part15_banner.png 650w,\n/static/0a29e347cf7b36c29637cdb3feebcdc2/8ff1e/part15_banner.png 800w\" src=\"/static/0a29e347cf7b36c29637cdb3feebcdc2/dbb61/part15_banner.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></p>\n<p>In the last part of the tutorial series, we&#x2019;re going to wrap up the Theme Settings. We&#x2019;ll finish up the two remaining fieldsets &#x2013; Home Page Settings and Footer Settings.</p>\n<p>Let&#x2019;s giv&#x2019;er!</p>\n<p><!--more--></p>\n<p><!------------------------STEP 1-----------------------------></p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">1. Home Page Settings</h2>\n<p>We&#x2019;re going to add a couple of dropdowns that allows the user to select which page and collection to display on the home page.</p>\n<p>Inside the fieldset for Home Page Settings, insert the code in red below:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n<fieldset>\n  <legend>Home Page Settings</legend>\n  <span style=\"color:red;\"><table>\n    <tbody><tr>\n      <th><label for=\"frontpage_homepage\">Page to show on homepage</label></th>\n      <td><select class=\"page\" name=\"frontpage_homepage\" id=\"frontpage_homepage\"></select></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th><label for=\"frontpage_collection\">Collection to show on homepage</label></th>\n      <td><select name=\"frontpage_collection\" class=\"collection\"></select></td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody></table></span>\n</fieldset>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>Notice the two classes that are being applied to the selects: &#x201C;page&#x201D; and &#x201C;collection&#x201D;. This will make it so that the dropdowns are pre-filled with the pages and collections of the shop, as seen in Figure 15.1 below.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/home-page-1.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:40.273972602739725%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/c768913f4e89a733f00547450f2524ce/aca85/home-page-1.jpg 163w,\n/static/c768913f4e89a733f00547450f2524ce/0954f/home-page-1.jpg 325w,\n/static/c768913f4e89a733f00547450f2524ce/a111b/home-page-1.jpg 650w,\n/static/c768913f4e89a733f00547450f2524ce/ce471/home-page-1.jpg 975w,\n/static/c768913f4e89a733f00547450f2524ce/20df9/home-page-1.jpg 1095w\" src=\"/static/c768913f4e89a733f00547450f2524ce/a111b/home-page-1.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/c768913f4e89a733f00547450f2524ce/aca85/home-page-1.jpg 163w,\n/static/c768913f4e89a733f00547450f2524ce/0954f/home-page-1.jpg 325w,\n/static/c768913f4e89a733f00547450f2524ce/a111b/home-page-1.jpg 650w,\n/static/c768913f4e89a733f00547450f2524ce/ce471/home-page-1.jpg 975w,\n/static/c768913f4e89a733f00547450f2524ce/20df9/home-page-1.jpg 1095w\" src=\"/static/c768913f4e89a733f00547450f2524ce/a111b/home-page-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 15.1: Dropdowns using the special class &#x201C;page&#x201D; and &#x201C;collection&#x201D;</div>\n<p>Next we&#x2019;ll tell the index.liquid template to load the page and collection selected in our new Theme Settings. Open index.liquid, and look for this line of code:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n{% assign page = pages.frontpage %}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>&#x2026; and replace with:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n{% assign page = pages.[settings.frontpage_homepage] %}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>We&#x2019;ll then add an if-statement that checks if any page has been selected. We do this by seeing if the value of page.handle is NOT blank (&#x201C;&#x201D;). Add the code in red below:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n{% assign page = pages.[settings.frontpage_homepage] %}\n<span style=\"color:red;\">{% if page.handle != &quot;&quot; %}</span>\n<div class=\"rte index-page\">\n    <h2>{{ page.title }}</h2>\n    {{ page.content }}\n</div>\n<span style=\"color:red;\">{% endif %}</span>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>Now let&#x2019;s do the same for the selected collection. Look for the block of code below:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n{% assign collection = collections.frontpage %}\n<div class=\"index-collection clearfix\">\n  <h2>{{ collection.title }}</h2>\n    {% for product in collection.products | limit:8 %}\n      {% include &apos;product-loop&apos; %}\n    {% endfor %}\n</div>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>and replace with:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n<span style=\"color:red;\">{% assign collection = collections.[settings.frontpage_collection] %}\n{% if collection.handle != &quot;&quot; %}\n<div class=\"index-collection clearfix\">\n  <h2>{{ collection.title }}</h2>\n    {% for product in collections.[collection.handle].products | limit:8 %}\n      {% include &apos;product-loop&apos; %}\n    {% endfor %}\n</div>\n{% endif %}</span>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>Now, if you go back to your Theme Settings and select a page and collection to show, you can select what page and collection you want to show on your homepage &#x1F642;</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/homepage-settings.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:92.27053140096618%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/9b79b5a2267efa97a8c4e936b8db468e/aca85/homepage-settings.jpg 163w,\n/static/9b79b5a2267efa97a8c4e936b8db468e/0954f/homepage-settings.jpg 325w,\n/static/9b79b5a2267efa97a8c4e936b8db468e/a111b/homepage-settings.jpg 650w,\n/static/9b79b5a2267efa97a8c4e936b8db468e/ce471/homepage-settings.jpg 975w,\n/static/9b79b5a2267efa97a8c4e936b8db468e/c8cd5/homepage-settings.jpg 1035w\" src=\"/static/9b79b5a2267efa97a8c4e936b8db468e/a111b/homepage-settings.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/9b79b5a2267efa97a8c4e936b8db468e/aca85/homepage-settings.jpg 163w,\n/static/9b79b5a2267efa97a8c4e936b8db468e/0954f/homepage-settings.jpg 325w,\n/static/9b79b5a2267efa97a8c4e936b8db468e/a111b/homepage-settings.jpg 650w,\n/static/9b79b5a2267efa97a8c4e936b8db468e/ce471/homepage-settings.jpg 975w,\n/static/9b79b5a2267efa97a8c4e936b8db468e/c8cd5/homepage-settings.jpg 1035w\" src=\"/static/9b79b5a2267efa97a8c4e936b8db468e/a111b/homepage-settings.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 15.2: The page and collection selected in the Theme Settings are now shown on the homepage</div>\n<p>Finally, let&#x2019;s add a select with custom options, for practice&#x2019;s sake :). We&#x2019;ll go ahead and add a dropdown that allows users to choose how many products they want to show on the homepage.</p>\n<p>Open settings.html, and add the following code in red.</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n...\n  \n    <label for=\"frontpage_collection\">Collection to show on homepage</label>\n    <select name=\"frontpage_collection\" class=\"collection\">\n   \n  \n    # of Products to show\n    \n      </select>\n          <option value=\"4\">4</option>\n          <option value=\"8\">8</option>\n          <option value=\"12\">12</option>\n          <option value=\"16\">16</option>                              \n      \n    \n  \n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>This will output a select dropdown with our own options (Figure 15.3).</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/number-of-products-setting.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:40.81255771006463%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/931e4e0cdad3b4b1e36bda7ed22acdb7/aca85/number-of-products-setting.jpg 163w,\n/static/931e4e0cdad3b4b1e36bda7ed22acdb7/0954f/number-of-products-setting.jpg 325w,\n/static/931e4e0cdad3b4b1e36bda7ed22acdb7/a111b/number-of-products-setting.jpg 650w,\n/static/931e4e0cdad3b4b1e36bda7ed22acdb7/ce471/number-of-products-setting.jpg 975w,\n/static/931e4e0cdad3b4b1e36bda7ed22acdb7/c021e/number-of-products-setting.jpg 1083w\" src=\"/static/931e4e0cdad3b4b1e36bda7ed22acdb7/a111b/number-of-products-setting.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/931e4e0cdad3b4b1e36bda7ed22acdb7/aca85/number-of-products-setting.jpg 163w,\n/static/931e4e0cdad3b4b1e36bda7ed22acdb7/0954f/number-of-products-setting.jpg 325w,\n/static/931e4e0cdad3b4b1e36bda7ed22acdb7/a111b/number-of-products-setting.jpg 650w,\n/static/931e4e0cdad3b4b1e36bda7ed22acdb7/ce471/number-of-products-setting.jpg 975w,\n/static/931e4e0cdad3b4b1e36bda7ed22acdb7/c021e/number-of-products-setting.jpg 1083w\" src=\"/static/931e4e0cdad3b4b1e36bda7ed22acdb7/a111b/number-of-products-setting.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 15.3: Custom select dropdown for number of products</div>\n<p>Now back in index.liquid, look for this line of code:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n    {% for product in collections.[collection.handle].products | limit:8 %}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>Replace the value for the &#x201C;limit&#x201D; with the theme setting variable, as shown below.</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n    {% for product in collections.[collection.handle].products | limit: <span style=\"color:red;\">settings.num_products</span> %}\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>Now, on your homepage, you will see a maximum of 4, 8, 12 or 16 products depending on what you selected in the Theme Settings.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/limit-.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:96.61016949152541%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/41473de6c865804e3223b76ac285ad93/aca85/limit-.jpg 163w,\n/static/41473de6c865804e3223b76ac285ad93/0954f/limit-.jpg 325w,\n/static/41473de6c865804e3223b76ac285ad93/a111b/limit-.jpg 650w,\n/static/41473de6c865804e3223b76ac285ad93/ce471/limit-.jpg 975w,\n/static/41473de6c865804e3223b76ac285ad93/1bb28/limit-.jpg 1003w\" src=\"/static/41473de6c865804e3223b76ac285ad93/a111b/limit-.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/41473de6c865804e3223b76ac285ad93/aca85/limit-.jpg 163w,\n/static/41473de6c865804e3223b76ac285ad93/0954f/limit-.jpg 325w,\n/static/41473de6c865804e3223b76ac285ad93/a111b/limit-.jpg 650w,\n/static/41473de6c865804e3223b76ac285ad93/ce471/limit-.jpg 975w,\n/static/41473de6c865804e3223b76ac285ad93/1bb28/limit-.jpg 1003w\" src=\"/static/41473de6c865804e3223b76ac285ad93/a111b/limit-.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 15.4: The homepage now shows the number of products selected in the Theme Settings, as opposed to the hardcoded limit (8) that we had earlier.</div>\n<p><!------------------------STEP 2-----------------------------></p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">2. Footer Settings</h2>\n<p>Let&#x2019;s add some settings in our Footer Settings for showing/hiding social icons. To do this, we&#x2019;ll use some checkboxes and a textfield, which are input types that we haven&#x2019;t used yet &#x1F642;</p>\n<p>Start off by saving the three images below to your computer, and then uploading them to your Template Editor&#x2019;s theme assets.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/icon-twitter.png\" style=\"padding-right:20px;\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:100%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 32px) 100vw, 32px\" srcset=\"/static/b62ee772c64dda641d95864e3ef114b0/cbd68/icon-twitter.png 32w\" src=\"/static/b62ee772c64dda641d95864e3ef114b0/cbd68/icon-twitter.png\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 32px) 100vw, 32px\" srcset=\"/static/b62ee772c64dda641d95864e3ef114b0/cbd68/icon-twitter.png 32w\" src=\"/static/b62ee772c64dda641d95864e3ef114b0/cbd68/icon-twitter.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/icon-pinterest.png\" style=\"padding-right:20px;\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:100%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 32px) 100vw, 32px\" srcset=\"/static/a2b3697925c1a07e82dfc26d086302ce/cbd68/icon-pinterest.png 32w\" src=\"/static/a2b3697925c1a07e82dfc26d086302ce/cbd68/icon-pinterest.png\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 32px) 100vw, 32px\" srcset=\"/static/a2b3697925c1a07e82dfc26d086302ce/cbd68/icon-pinterest.png 32w\" src=\"/static/a2b3697925c1a07e82dfc26d086302ce/cbd68/icon-pinterest.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/icon-fb.png\" style=\"padding-right:20px;\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:100%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 32px) 100vw, 32px\" srcset=\"/static/4347aea7babde2aaff3de21d7de30c22/cbd68/icon-fb.png 32w\" src=\"/static/4347aea7babde2aaff3de21d7de30c22/cbd68/icon-fb.png\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 32px) 100vw, 32px\" srcset=\"/static/4347aea7babde2aaff3de21d7de30c22/cbd68/icon-fb.png 32w\" src=\"/static/4347aea7babde2aaff3de21d7de30c22/cbd68/icon-fb.png\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<p>After uploading, make sure the icons can be found in your theme assets (Figure 15.5).</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/uploaded-icons.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:58.70967741935484%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/b12c7f03a5ccfe861630c604b7e5a202/aca85/uploaded-icons.jpg 163w,\n/static/b12c7f03a5ccfe861630c604b7e5a202/0954f/uploaded-icons.jpg 325w,\n/static/b12c7f03a5ccfe861630c604b7e5a202/a111b/uploaded-icons.jpg 650w,\n/static/b12c7f03a5ccfe861630c604b7e5a202/ce471/uploaded-icons.jpg 975w,\n/static/b12c7f03a5ccfe861630c604b7e5a202/23787/uploaded-icons.jpg 1085w\" src=\"/static/b12c7f03a5ccfe861630c604b7e5a202/a111b/uploaded-icons.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/b12c7f03a5ccfe861630c604b7e5a202/aca85/uploaded-icons.jpg 163w,\n/static/b12c7f03a5ccfe861630c604b7e5a202/0954f/uploaded-icons.jpg 325w,\n/static/b12c7f03a5ccfe861630c604b7e5a202/a111b/uploaded-icons.jpg 650w,\n/static/b12c7f03a5ccfe861630c604b7e5a202/ce471/uploaded-icons.jpg 975w,\n/static/b12c7f03a5ccfe861630c604b7e5a202/23787/uploaded-icons.jpg 1085w\" src=\"/static/b12c7f03a5ccfe861630c604b7e5a202/a111b/uploaded-icons.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 15.5: The icons should be in the &#x201C;assets&#x201D; folder</div>\n<p>Open settings.html. Under the fieldset for &#x201C;Footer Settings&#x201D;, add the code in red below.</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n<fieldset>\n  <legend>Footer Settings</legend>\n  <span style=\"color:red;\"><table>\n    <tbody><tr>\n      <td><label for=\"facebook_show\">Show Facebook Icon</label></td>      \n      <td><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"facebook_show\" name=\"facebook_show\" value=\"1\" checked=\"checked\"></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th><label for=\"facebook_link\">Facebook Link</label></th>\n      <td><input type=\"text\" id=\"facebook_link\" name=\"facebook_link\" value></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td><label for=\"twitter_show\">Show Twitter Icon</label></td>      \n      <td><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"twitter_show\" name=\"twitter_show\" value=\"1\" checked=\"checked\"></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td><label for=\"twitter_link\">Twitter Link</label></td>\n      <td><input type=\"text\" id=\"twitter_link\" name=\"twitter_link\" value></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td><label for=\"pinterest_show\">Show Pinterest Icon</label></td>      \n      <td><input type=\"checkbox\" id=\"pinterest_show\" name=\"pinterest_show\" value=\"1\" checked=\"checked\"></td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th><label for=\"pinterest_link\">Pinterest Link</label></th>\n      <td><input type=\"text\" id=\"pinterest_link\" name=\"pinterest_link\" value></td>\n    </tr>       \n  </tbody></table></span>\n</fieldset>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>You will now see checkboxes for hiding/showing the icons, as well as a textbox for entering the URL of their respective pages. Go ahead and check the checkboxes, plug in some URLs for the icons, and hit Save.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/social-settings.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:48.71086556169429%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/fe4f891080fab1c6554e58284f9948d8/aca85/social-settings.jpg 163w,\n/static/fe4f891080fab1c6554e58284f9948d8/0954f/social-settings.jpg 325w,\n/static/fe4f891080fab1c6554e58284f9948d8/a111b/social-settings.jpg 650w,\n/static/fe4f891080fab1c6554e58284f9948d8/ce471/social-settings.jpg 975w,\n/static/fe4f891080fab1c6554e58284f9948d8/aacd8/social-settings.jpg 1086w\" src=\"/static/fe4f891080fab1c6554e58284f9948d8/a111b/social-settings.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/fe4f891080fab1c6554e58284f9948d8/aca85/social-settings.jpg 163w,\n/static/fe4f891080fab1c6554e58284f9948d8/0954f/social-settings.jpg 325w,\n/static/fe4f891080fab1c6554e58284f9948d8/a111b/social-settings.jpg 650w,\n/static/fe4f891080fab1c6554e58284f9948d8/ce471/social-settings.jpg 975w,\n/static/fe4f891080fab1c6554e58284f9948d8/aacd8/social-settings.jpg 1086w\" src=\"/static/fe4f891080fab1c6554e58284f9948d8/a111b/social-settings.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 15.6: Theme Settings for social icons</div>\n<p>Let&#x2019;s now add some code to output the icons. Open theme.liquid, and insert the code in red below:</p>\n<pre><code markup=\"span\">\n  <footer>\n      <ul>\n        {% for link in linklists.footer.links %}\n        <li><a href=\"{{ link.url }}\">{{ link.title }}</a></li>\n        {% endfor %}\n      </ul>\n      <span style=\"color:red;\"><div class=\"social\">\n        {% if settings.facebook_show %}<a href=\"{{ settings.facebook_link }}\"><img src=\"{{ &apos;icon-fb.png&apos; | asset_url }}\"></a>{% endif %}\n        {% if settings.twitter_show %}<a href=\"{{ settings.twitter_link }}\"><img src=\"{{ &apos;icon-twitter.png&apos; | asset_url }}\"></a>{% endif %}\n        {% if settings.pinterest_show %}<a href=\"{{ settings.pinterest_link }}\"><img src=\"{{ &apos;icon-pinterest.png&apos; | asset_url }}\"></a>{% endif %}\n      </div></span>\n    </footer>\n</code>\n</pre>\n<p>There is an if statement that wraps the social icon images that checks if the checkbox for that particular is icon is selected. If it is checked, it will go ahead and output the icon. The icon is also wrapped with an anchor tag that has an attribute set to the value of the textbox for that icon.</p>\n<p>You&#x2019;ll now see the social icons in your footer.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.tetchi.ca/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/footer-icons.jpg\"><div class=\" gatsby-image-wrapper\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;max-width:100%\" data-reactroot><div style=\"width:100%;padding-bottom:33.36575875486381%\"></div><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition-delay:500ms\"><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/4976cda84c0d14c4403122c46e05538a/aca85/footer-icons.jpg 163w,\n/static/4976cda84c0d14c4403122c46e05538a/0954f/footer-icons.jpg 325w,\n/static/4976cda84c0d14c4403122c46e05538a/a111b/footer-icons.jpg 650w,\n/static/4976cda84c0d14c4403122c46e05538a/ce471/footer-icons.jpg 975w,\n/static/4976cda84c0d14c4403122c46e05538a/2d8ff/footer-icons.jpg 1028w\" src=\"/static/4976cda84c0d14c4403122c46e05538a/a111b/footer-icons.jpg\" alt style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center;opacity:1;transition:opacity 500ms\"></picture><noscript><picture><img sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" srcset=\"/static/4976cda84c0d14c4403122c46e05538a/aca85/footer-icons.jpg 163w,\n/static/4976cda84c0d14c4403122c46e05538a/0954f/footer-icons.jpg 325w,\n/static/4976cda84c0d14c4403122c46e05538a/a111b/footer-icons.jpg 650w,\n/static/4976cda84c0d14c4403122c46e05538a/ce471/footer-icons.jpg 975w,\n/static/4976cda84c0d14c4403122c46e05538a/2d8ff/footer-icons.jpg 1028w\" src=\"/static/4976cda84c0d14c4403122c46e05538a/a111b/footer-icons.jpg\" alt=\"\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;opacity:1;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;object-position:center\"/></picture></noscript></div></a></p>\n<div class=\"sub\">Figure 15.7: Social icons output in the footer</div>\n<p><!------------------------ DONE -----------------------------></p>\n<h2 class=\"step\">The End</h2>\n<p>That&#x2019;s it that&#x2019;s all! You now have a basic, fully-functional Shopify theme. I hope this was helpful and serves as a good basis for you to build your own kickass theme.</p>\n<p>Cheers and thanks for reading!</p>\n<p>Tetchi</p>\n<p><a href=\"/shopify-theme-from-scratch/\">&#x2190; Back to table of contents</a>\t\t</p>\n</body></html>","wordpress_id":3793},"allWordpressWpComments":{"edges":[{"node":{"content":"<p>Firstly, thanks for such a great tutorial, it was a huge help for me with starting to make shopify themes.<br />\nSecondly, I don&#8217;t suppose you have / are planning on doing a responsive tutorial for this are you?</p>\n<p>Thanks</p>\n","author_name":"Leanne","date":"December 15th, 2015"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Back again, I managed to figure out everything except the drop down menu part.</p>\n","author_name":"Jeannie","date":"March 1st, 2015"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Although Shopify has updated its site, I was able to follow your instructions fairly easily. However, I uploaded the three social icons through &#8220;Files&#8221; but they do not appear in my Assets menu. How do I get them there?<br />\nI&#8217;m still trying to get my collections to appear in a drop down menu under catalog. Or show all the collections available to choose from on the catalog page.<br />\nI notice that most of your other comments are somewhat old so I hope you are still moderating this site. Thanks for the tutorial!</p>\n","author_name":"Jeannie","date":"February 28th, 2015"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Hey Tetsuro, thank you very much for your detailed step-by-step explanations and code samples. This is absolutely an invaluable tutorial. As a person who is trying to learn to code in Liquid, this the best and only detailed one I found around. I appreciate the time you put in. Cheers!</p>\n","author_name":"Joe","date":"February 27th, 2015"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Thanks so much for doing this, tetchi, I really appreciate all the work you&#8217;ve done on this. Where can I click to buy you a beer?</p>\n","author_name":"Tracy","date":"February 25th, 2015"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Fantastic job on this tutorial!<br />\nVery helpful and greatly expanded my understanding of liquid and the shopify customizing methods in general.</p>\n","author_name":"Gordon","date":"February 1st, 2015"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Simply awesome &#8211; well written, easy to follow tutorial. </p>\n<p>I owe you a drink 🙂</p>\n","author_name":"Raj","date":"October 22nd, 2014"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Thanks for all the tutorials, there were certainly loads there that I hadn&#8217;t seen before!</p>\n<p>good work sir!</p>\n","author_name":"Luke","date":"June 6th, 2014"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Thanks for the kind words Toby, have a good one 🙂</p>\n","author_name":"tetchi","date":"April 6th, 2014"}},{"node":{"content":"<p>Thanks so much for these tutorials, In 3 days, I&#8217;ve worked through all the 15 tutorials and gone from knowing absolutely nothing about shopify, to now feeling confident enough to go off and create my own theme! watch this space! thanks so much for the great tutorials</p>\n","author_name":"Toby Powell","date":"April 4th, 